      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "No, finishing only the first few days or even half the total course is not considered a reasonable compromise because it leaves a dangerous gap in treatment. This partial course, taken immediately after symptoms clear, is the most effective way to trigger the rapid development of antibiotic resistance. Even though it feels like a small short-term trade-off, your doctor prescribed the full duration to guarantee you get the best possible chance of total recovery without future complications.",
      "source": "target",
